{"body": "Also, thinking about it, the block passed to `cache_if` is semantically opposite of the block passed to `link_to_if` (likewise for `*_unless`).  That is: `cache_if` evaluates the block if the condition is true, but `link_to_if` evaluates the block if the condition is false.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/11406955", "created_at": "2012-12-15T17:35:50Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/8497#issuecomment-11406955", "updated_at": "2012-12-15T17:35:50Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 8497, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonathanhefner/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonathanhefner/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonathanhefner/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonathanhefner", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonathanhefner/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/jonathanhefner", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonathanhefner/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/1b4dce70c60dd89d5d316e02fb64f4ef?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F339667490c94f27251379643cab66025.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonathanhefner/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonathanhefner/received_events", "gravatar_id": "1b4dce70c60dd89d5d316e02fb64f4ef", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonathanhefner/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "jonathanhefner", "type": "User", "id": 771968, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonathanhefner/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523d8735bd354364b900792c"}, "id": 11406955, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/8497"}
